  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Supply Chain Planner",
  "description": "<p>At <strong>Maison 21G</strong>, we craft emotion through scent — blending creativity, precision, and innovation to create meaningful luxury experiences for B2B customers and B2C. As our lifestyle and retail footprint continues to grow across the world, we are looking for a <strong>Supply Chain Planner</strong> who is curious, detail-driven, and excited to be part of a fast-moving, design-led brand.</p><p>This role is ideal for an early-career professional who enjoys problem-solving, working with data, and collaborating across teams to bring products from concept to customer seamlessly.<br /></p><p><strong>What You’ll Do</strong></p><p><strong>B2C Supply Chain & Planning</strong></p><ul><li>Drive the <strong>S&OP cycle</strong> for our B2B and B2C business across travel retail, distributors, retail stores, and e-commerce.</li><li>Manage end-to-end <strong>inventory planning</strong> for raw materials and components.</li><li>Lead <strong>demand forecasting and analysis</strong>, ensuring optimal stock levels.</li><li>Prepare <strong>reorder recommendations</strong> based on forecasts, lead times, MOQ, and current inventory.</li><li>Coordinate closely with raw material suppliers (scent concentrates, alcohol, DPG), including PO management and delivery follow-ups.</li><li>Participate in weekly <strong>Inventory & Planning meetings</strong>, documenting actions and ensuring follow-through.</li><li>Maintain and improve production planning tools, inventory trackers, and scheduling frameworks — with a focus on <strong>automation and accuracy</strong>.</li><li>Act as a key point of contact for distributors and travel retail partners on day-to-day supply matters.</li></ul><p><strong>B2B Supply Chain Support</strong></p><ul><li>Contribute to weekly <strong>S&OP meetings</strong>, sharing insights and updates across projects.</li><li>Oversee <strong>oil stock management</strong> and coordinate between warehouses and subcontractors in China (perfume, candles, and ancillary factories)</li></ul><p><strong>Who You Are</strong></p><ul><li>Master's or Bachelor’s degree in <strong>Supply Chain, Business, or a related field</strong>.</li><li><strong>2-3 years of experience</strong> in supply chain, logistics, or operations</li><li>Analytical, structured, and highly detail-oriented.</li><li>Confident with advanced <strong>Excel</strong> and comfortable working with data.</li><li>Proactive, organized, and collaborative, you thrive in dynamic and fast pace environments.</li><li>Problem solving, agile</li></ul>",
